This paper is about scaling Software Defined Networking (SDN) controllers, which is a topic related to computer networks and distributed systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of functional slicing, which is a technique for dividing applications into smaller, more manageable pieces, and this is a topic related to programming languages and compilers. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category. Other possible categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as these categories are also related to distributed systems and network security, which are topics discussed in the paper.
